    <h2>MCP proxy</h2>
    <p>Proxy external MCP servers through the kernel. Configure servers in your HUMANFILE, and agents call them through <code>ostk mcp call</code> — compressed, audited, with secrets injected from the platform keychain.</p>
    <pre><code># HUMANFILE
mcp:
  linear: npx -y @anthropic/linear-mcp-server
  github: gh mcp-server

# Agent calls
ostk mcp list                        # show configured servers
ostk mcp call linear list-issues     # call a tool</code></pre>
    <p>Servers prefixed <code>fcp-*</code> run as persistent driver daemons — the subprocess stays alive between calls, preserving workspace state (LSP, analyzer caches). All other servers spawn per-call.</p>

    <h2>TUI</h2>
    <p>The TUI is the operator console. It shows the OS working — agents executing needles, file writes resolving, permissions gating dangerous operations. Everything the kernel does is visible here in real time.</p>
    <pre><code>ostk tui</code></pre>

    <div class="tui-showcase">
