        <figcaption>Agent workflow — the scheduler executes →896 and →897 sequentially. Each file edit shows <code>[✓] Edit edit applied</code>. The status bar tracks: elapsed time, tool count, agent identity, model, context usage, and cost.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure class="tui-figure">
        <img src="/images/tui/tui-permission-modal.jpg" alt="TUI permission modal — scheduler requests Bash access with allow, deny, and always-allow options" class="tui-screenshot" />
        <figcaption>Permission gate — the <code>:approval</code> system. Agents request tool access. The operator sees exactly what will run and chooses: <code>[y]</code> allow once, <code>[n]</code> deny, <code>[a]</code> always allow for this tool. No silent execution.</figcaption>
      </figure>
