    <h2>Semantic compression</h2>
    <p>Embeddings-powered deduplication saves more tokens by detecting semantically similar output, not just identical lines.</p>
    <pre><code># Download the embeddings model (potion-base-8M from HuggingFace)
ostk embeddings download

# The kernel uses it automatically once available.
# Boot prints guidance if the model is missing.</code></pre>

    <h2>ostk should</h2>
    <p>File bugs and features in natural language. The OS compiles your intent into structured needles.</p>
    <pre><code>ostk should "fix the auth flow when tokens expire"
ostk should "add retry logic to the API client"</code></pre>

    <h2>Downloads</h2>
    <p>Latest release: <strong>v2.3.0</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/os-tack/ostk.ai/releases/tag/v2.3.0" onclick="plausible('Download', {props: {target: 'release-page'}})">ostk v2.3.0 release</a> — macOS arm64/x86_64, Linux musl arm64/x86_64, GPG .asc signatures</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Or install via script (always fetches latest): <a href="https://ostk.ai/install" onclick="plausible('Install', {props: {method: 'curl'}})">view install script</a></p>
    <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://ostk.ai/install | sh</code></pre>

    <h2>Governance</h2>
    <p>ostk uses a layered governance model. Each layer is a signed file that defines authority, preferences, and behavior.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/humanfile">HUMANFILE</a> — operator identity, tack dialect, preferences. GPG-signed by the human.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/entityfile">ENTITYFILE</a> — instance governance. Defines trust tiers, authority chain, kernel attestation.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/agentfile">Agentfile</a> — agent process descriptor. FROM, BOOT, TOOL, LIMIT, WORK directives.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/osfile">OSfile</a> — OS identity carrier. The signed binary + primefile = OS identity.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/secrets">Secrets</a> — OS-mediated secret resolution. API keys never enter LLM context.</li>
    </ul>

